Registry for managing remote machines in federation.

## Data Model

```go
type Machine struct {
    Name     string `json:"name"`
    Type     string `json:"type"`      // "local", "ssh", "gcp"
    Host     string `json:"host"`      // for ssh: user@host
    KeyPath  string `json:"key_path"`  // SSH key path
    TownPath string `json:"town_path"` // Path to town on remote
}
```

## Interface

```go
type MachineRegistry struct {
    path     string  // config/federation.json
    machines map[string]*Machine
}

func NewMachineRegistry(configPath string) *MachineRegistry
func (r *MachineRegistry) Get(name string) (*Machine, error)
func (r *MachineRegistry) Add(m *Machine) error
func (r *MachineRegistry) Remove(name string) error
func (r *MachineRegistry) List() []*Machine
func (r *MachineRegistry) Connection(name string) (Connection, error)
```

## Storage

federation.json in config/:
```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "machines": {
    "local": {"type": "local"},
    "gcp-vm-1": {
      "type": "ssh",
      "host": "user@10.0.0.1",
      "key_path": "~/.ssh/gcp_key",
      "town_path": "/home/user/ai"
    }
  }
}
```

## Connection Factory

```go
func (r *MachineRegistry) Connection(name string) (Connection, error) {
    m := r.machines[name]
    switch m.Type {
    case "local":
        return NewLocalConnection(), nil
    case "ssh":
        return NewSSHConnection(m.Host, m.KeyPath), nil
    }
}
```

Manage integration branches for swarm merging strategy.

## Branch Naming

- Integration branch: `integration/<swarm-id>` (e.g., integration/sw-1)
- Worker branches: `<swarm-id>/<polecat>` (e.g., sw-1/Toast)

## Operations

```go
// Create integration branch at swarm start
func (m *SwarmManager) CreateIntegrationBranch(swarmID string) error
// - Creates from BaseCommit
// - Pushes to origin

// Merge worker branch to integration
func (r *Refinery) MergeToIntegration(swarmID, workerBranch string) error
// - Fetches worker branch
// - Merges to integration/<swarm-id>
// - Handles conflicts (semantic merge)

// Land integration to main
func (r *Refinery) LandToMain(swarmID string) error
// - Merges integration/<swarm-id> to main
// - Pushes to origin
// - Triggers cleanup

// Cleanup branches after landing
func (m *SwarmManager) CleanupBranches(swarmID string) error
// - Deletes integration/<swarm-id> (local + remote)
// - Deletes all <swarm-id>/<polecat> branches
```

## All Workers Same Base

When swarm starts:
1. Record current main HEAD as BaseCommit
2. All polecats branch from BaseCommit
3. Integration branch also starts at BaseCommit

This ensures clean merges within the swarm.

